    if (SA->hasNoUnsignedWrap()) {
      // If the addition does not unsign overflow then we can, by definition,
      // commute the zero extension with the addition operation.
      // However, we must ensure that the zero-extended addition also doesn't
      // overflow in the wider type. This requires that each operand's
      // zero-extended value plus the sum of others doesn't exceed 2^W-1.
      // For simplicity, we only apply this transformation when we can prove
